        "Answer": "The petition must be dismissed. The power of the DAR to issue the AO is valid. The power to prescribe qualifications for public office is not exclusively legislative. The Civil Service Commission, as the central personnel agency of the government, is empowered to prescribe all qualifications for any position in the civil service. The DAR, as an administrative agency, may be validly authorized by law to issue rules and regulations to carry out its mandate."
