        "Question": "What is the concept of expanded judicial review under the 1987 Constitution?",
        "Answer": "The concept of expanded judicial review of the Supreme Court, the facial challenge to the constitutionality laws is no longer limited to laws which violate the freedom of speech but applies to all violations of fundamental rights under the Bill of Rights. In addition, the remedies of certiorari and prohibition in the Supreme Court are broader in scope and may be issued to correct errors of jurisdiction of judicial, quasi-judicial, or ministerial actions and may be invoked to restrain any act of grave abuse of discretion of any branch of government."
